## Errors & Mistakes
- BIGGEST: I repeatedly clobbered my own test runs. Single-process pytest
  sessions all use ClickHouse DB `<base>_test` (xdist workers use _wN), and
  the session fixture DROPs+recreates that DB at start. Running the
  trace_server shard in the background while launching openai/flask runs in
  the foreground produced "3 passed, 24 errors" and "1086 passed, 229
  errors" that looked like real regressions. All passed once serialized.
  Future agents: NEVER run two non-xdist pytest sessions concurrently here.
- My first marker inventory used `| head -60` and I concluded only 5 files
  used skip_clickhouse_client. A later accidental `rg -rn` (-r is
  --replace! output-only rewrite, files untouched) revealed ~30 files. The
  decorator strip then had to be redone repo-wide.
- Wrong test name guess (test_openai_quickstart_with_stream doesn't exist)
  plus `| tail` masking pytest's exit code made the first VCR experiment
  read as a false success ("collected 1 item / 0 ran", exit 0 via tail).
- `git stash -u` for an A/B check collided with a transient Conductor git
  index.lock — scary output ("stash entry kept") but no stash was created
  and the working tree was intact. Switched to `git worktree add` for the
  A/B instead (clean).
- Edit-tool friction: my own bulk python rewrites invalidated tracked file
  state mid-batch (test_orm.py), and Bash `sed -n`/cat reads don't satisfy
  the Edit tool's read-before-write (test_digest_validation.py,
  test_rescore_evaluation.py). Re-read via Read tool and reapplied.
- zsh ate `====FOO` separators in compound commands (treated as glob/eq);
  use quoted echo markers.

