## Hints for Future Agents
- pysqlite3 (pyproject langchain extra), libsqlite3-dev apt steps, and the
  dependabot pysqlite3* entry are for CHROMADB (langchain shard), not the
  trace server. langchain_test.py sys.modules-swaps sqlite3→pysqlite3 per
  chroma's troubleshooting doc. Do not remove. Origin: 6c559b71e2.
- tests/integrations VCR config (ignore_localhost: True, ignore api.wandb.ai)
  is what makes client-fixture VCR tests CH-compatible. If a VCR test fails
  on CH with CannotOverwriteExistingCassetteException, check whether the
  request is to an EXTERNAL host (cassette drift) before blaming CH: the
  huggingface failure here was huggingface_hub adding
  ?expand=inferenceProviderMapping, reproducible on any backend.
- test_flask_server (tests/trace/test_weave_client_threaded.py) fails on
  this macOS box on a pristine HEAD worktree ("Server disconnected without
  sending a response") — environmental, not change-related.
- --trace-server=prod and =http in tests/conftest.py create_client look
  half-broken (http passes the literal flag as URL) and now ALSO raise in
  the trace_server fixture for non-clickhouse flags. If anyone needs them,
  they must bypass/skip the trace_server fixture dependency.
- windows_trace_tests deletion = Windows loses ALL trace-server-marked test
  coverage (Linux-container CH can't run on GH Windows runners). If this is
  unacceptable, options: remote CH service for Windows jobs, or accept
  trace_no_server-only coverage (chosen here).
- The trace shard locally needs -m "trace_server" to match CI selection;
  without it you also pull no-server tests into the CH session.

## Codebase Discoveries
- pytest_collection_modifyitems in tests/trace_server/conftest.py marks
  trace_server both by path (tests/trace_server/) AND by fixture usage, so
  client-fixture tests anywhere get the marker — that's why the
  `-m "not trace_server"` sqlite fallback in get_trace_server_flag was
  effectively dead code.
- PreparedInsert.sql was only consumed by the sqlite path; the CH client
  inserts via (table, data, column_names).
- sqlite_trace_server re-exported errors.NotFoundError; tests aliasing it as
  sqliteNotFoundError were raising/catching the same class twice.
- compute_file_digest's canonical home is weave.shared.digest.
- The query_builder tests are pure SQL-string unit tests (no DB); they were
  marker-skipped on the CH leg purely to avoid double-running.

